[SN]TITLE[SN]
Why is the weather so hot and will it last?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Glorious sunshine and temperatures of up to 35 degrees in parts of the UK, but what is causing it?

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
19 July 2016 Last updated at 12:42 BST
A heatwave in Spain and a strong breeze could be bringing the hot weather north to the UK. This is called a Spanish plume.
This could also mean hot and humid storms later this week.
We spoke to our resident weather expert Simon King to find out more...
